Database:
Install the POSTGRESQl with docker container 
docker run --name postgresql-container -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=somePassword -d postgres
The above statement will install postgres and will run the system at port 5432
Install the PGADMIN 4 tools for the POSTGRES community for accessing the database
docker run --rm -p 5050:5050 thajeztah/pgadmin4
After this manage the PGADMIN 4 from http://localhost:5050 in the browser
